    "finalText": "Recent Teams retrieval is not reliable enough to trust as a complete source today.\n\nWhat I can confirm:\n- There’s a known retrieval gap for recent Teams messages: “There is a significant gap in the ability to retrieve recent Teams messages reliably; a dedicated recent message retrieval tool is needed” [ai_memory, 2026-05-19].\n- We do have evidence that Teams service itself was restored and messaging was functioning reliably after a browser issue, with redundant monitoring in place [Teams DM summary, 2026-04-30, referring to 2026-02-15 update].\n\nWhat that means:\n- **Platform uptime may be fine**\n- **Assistant-side retrieval of recent Teams messages is still not trustworthy as a complete source**\n\nSo the answer is: **treat Teams as potentially incomplete for “today” signal**. Good for partial context, not good enough to assume you’re seeing everything. [ai_memory, 2026-05-19; Teams DM summary, 2026-04-30]\n\nIf you want, I can still search Teams plus email and meetings together and tell you what’s confirmed versus what may be missing.",
